 149:                         pass


 150:                     def bad_gauss(mu, sigma, x):#bad

 155:             - **badvalue** Optional number. The value that will be used to

 310:             - :math:`E_i` is expected number of occupancy in ith bin from PDF


 311:               calculated using average of pdf value at both sides of the bin

 313:               extended likelihood is requested.


 314: 


 315:               If extended likelihood is requested (``extended=True``):


 316:

 321:
